Class IR_Election

  • java.lang.Object
    • main.Election
      • main.IR_Election
  • public class IR_Election
extends Election
    A class that represents an IR_Election and contains methods to run the entirity of IR_Election, produce an audit file, and display the winner of an IR_Election.

      • shuffleBallots

        public void shuffleBallots()
        Shuffles the array of ballots contained in IR_Election. Takes no parameters and returns nothing. A helper funtion for run()

      • run

        public void run()
         throws java.io.IOException
        Runs the IR algorithm and writes audit information to the audit file and displays the results and winner information of the election to the screen. Assumes the electionScanner begins on the second line, all information contained in the IR election ballot file is entered properly, there is at least one ballot in the file and at least one candidate. Takes no parameters and returns nothing. Generates an audit file. Assumes election class has been initalized properly and so has audit object.
        Overrides:
        run in class Election
        Throws:
        java.awt.print.PrinterException
        java.io.IOException - if write fails
